<LP>
   RICHARDSON, Texas -- Convex Computer Corp. announced a
three-year, $20 million contract with E-Systems Inc. of
Dallas.
   Convex will supply supercomputer equipment and services to
defense contractor E-Systems for a computer data storage
system called the E-Systems modular automated storage system,
or Emass. Convex C2 supercomputers will act as the main
controllers for Emass.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Emass is composed of a Convex supercomputer with magnetic
disks, a robotically controlled magnetic tape storage
subsystem and an operations console. Under the terms of the
agreement, Convex will provide hardware and system software
and will develop special interfaces that will be used with
the storage device.
